name: v0.10.36
body:
**Infracost v0.10.36**

This release primarily focuses on refining existing features, enhancing stability, and introducing new improvements. Key highlights include enhanced logging, updates to usage comments, various fixes to support accurate configurations, and the support for templates.

**What's New**

* **Refined log output** Infracost CLI now outputs a simpler and easy to follow log output. This aids with understanding how Infracost processes your projects ([#3003](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3003) by @hugorut )
* **Optimized Azure cost estimation:**  Experience more reliable calculations for Azure Dds v5 PostgreSQL Flexible Servers ([#3014](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3014) by @vdmgolub) and Azure Container Registry ([#3048](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3048) by @aliscott).
* **Streamlined commenting:** Reduced noise in Infracost comments through the removal of usage cost header links ([#3009](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3009) by @vdmgolub).
* **Expanded autodetection:** Support for wildcards in autodetect `envNames` for broadened file detection ([#3031](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3031) by @hugorut).
* **Robust environment variable handling:**  Support for '.' in environment variable file names ([#3032](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3032) by @aliscott) and proper recognition of hidden files ([#3033](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3033) by @aliscott).
* **Template file support:**  Utilize the `templatefile` function to introduce flexible customizations to your Terraform configurations ([#3041](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3041) by @hugorut).
* **Enhanced comments:** Receive more informative Infracost comments that explain skipped resources and projects by default.

**Fixes**

* **Prevented unnecessary panics:** Resolved an issue that could cause panics when calculating labels for blocks ([#2997](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2997) by @tim775).
* **Consistent directory association:**  Ensured correct association of child directories containing var files during autodetection ([#3000](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3000) by @hugorut).
* **Removed redundant feature flag:** Cleaned up code by removing the `usage api` feature flag ([#2999](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2999) by @tim775).
* **Corrected usage footnote:** Updated the usage footnote text for accuracy ([#3001](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3001) by @tim775) .
* **Prioritized error handling:** Fixed an issue where child resources were incorrectly removed ([#3019](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3019) by @tim775).
* **Corrected capacity and length ordering:** Fixed an issue causing capacity and length to be displayed in the wrong order ([#3039](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3039) by @aliscott).
* **Fixed configuration generation:** Corrected YAML indentation issues in generated config files ([#3034](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/3034) by @hugorut).

**We'd like to give a warm welcome to our new contributors:**  @verytrap, @hidewrong, @largemouth, @owenrumney

**For the complete changelog, please visit:**  [https://github.com/infracost/infracost/compare/v0.10.35...v0.10.36](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/compare/v0.10.35...v0.10.36)

name: v0.10.35
body:
## Infracost v0.10.35

This release focuses on support for usage based costs, and adding new cost estimation capabilities.

### New Features
* **Separate Usage Costs:** Add separate usage costs to comment (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2941 by @tim775).
* **Usage Type Defaults:** Add usage type defaults that targets $20 per key (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2938 by @tim775).
* **RDS Extended Support:** Add support for `RDS` `ExtendedSupport` cost component (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2933 by @hugorut).
* **EKS Extended Support:** Add eks extended support cost (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2935 by @hugorut).
* **Autodetect Configuration:** Add `force_project_type` configuration (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2942 by @hugorut).
* **Env Var Extensions:** Add support for `env_var_extensions` autodetect configuration (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2949 by @hugorut).
* **Azure Network DDoS Protection Plan:** Add support for `azurerm_network_ddos_protection_plan` (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2967 by @hugorut).
* **Azure App Configuration:** Add support for `azurerm_app_configuration` (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2970 by @hugorut).
* **Azure Federated Identity Credential:** Add support for `azurerm_federated_identity_credential` (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2974 by @hugorut).
* **Azure AI Services:** Add support for Azure AI services: Speech, OpenAI and LUIS (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2975 by @aliscott).
* **Azure AI Language:** Add support for Azure AI Language (TextAnalytics) (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2976 by @aliscott).
* **Project Config for Cloud Workspace and Org:** Add support project config for cloud workspace and org (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2993 by @hugorut).

### Enhancements

* **Usage File and Config File:** Allow --usage-file and --config-file to be used together (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2944 by @tim775).
* **Matching Files to Env Names:** Update matching files to env names to be case insensitive (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2957 by @aliscott).
* **Diff and Breakdown Sorting:** Sort diff and breakdown with most costly resources first (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2964 by @tim775).

### Fixes

* **Azure Cost Component Issues:** Fix various Azure cost component issues (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2934 by @aliscott).
* **Meta Attributes:** Don't evaluate or marshal `depends_on` or `lifecycle` meta attributes (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2936 by @aliscott).
* **Diff Test:** Fix failing diff test (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2950 by @hugorut).
* **Errored Projects:** Correctly show errored projects (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2955 by @tim775).
* **Azure Security Subscription Pricing:** Add missing usage schema to azure security subscription pricing (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2992 by @tim775).
* **Google Egress:** Set default usage to zero for google egress (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2991 by @tim775).

**For the complete changelog, visit:** https://github.com/infracost/infracost/compare/v0.10.34...v0.10.35

name: v0.10.34
body:
## Infracost v0.10.34

This release focuses on improving reliability, enhancing existing features, and adding new cost estimation capabilities.

### New Features

* **Configurable auto-detection:** Customize the maximum search depth for Terraform file discovery (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2926 by @hugorut).
* **Invalid API key handling:** Streamline your workflow with immediate notification of invalid Infracost API keys (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2927 by @hugorut).
* **Azure Machine Learning support:** Get cost estimates for Azure Machine Learning Compute Instances and Clusters (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2902  by @aliscott).

### Enhancements

* **HCL graph tests:**  Provide greater confidence in Infracost's cost calculations for complex Terraform deployments (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2783 by @hugorut and @aliscott ).
* **Robust error handling:** Improved dashboard API request retries and more graceful handling of governance failures (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2910, https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2913  by @tim775).
* **Consistent stack traces:** Aid debugging with sanitized stack trace matching (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2914 by @aliscott).
* **Improved usage reporting:** Ensure accurate usage data with correct handling of nested keys (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2912 by @tim775).
* **HCL parsing refinements:** Enhanced cost estimation accuracy by ensuring correct boolean return values (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2909 by @aliscott). 

### Fixes

* **Module handling:** Resolved issues with evaluating module variables, dependencies between modules, and loading mock providers (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2877, https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2925 by @aliscott, https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2903 by @tim775).
* **Azure fixes:**  Enabled support for Azure CosmosDB accounts referenced by name and Azure Redis with 0 shards (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2894, https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2905 by @aliscott).
* **Resource handling refinements:**  Addressed potential panics and issues with invalid files (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2891, https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2892 by @aliscott).
* **Cost comparison accuracy:**  Ensured correct display of 100% cost increases for previously empty projects (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2899 by @hugorut).
* **Terragrunt integration:**  Ignore duplicate block warnings from Terragrunt for a smoother experience (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2898 by @hugorut).
* **Improved AWS and GCP support:** Corrected AWS RDS example comments and optimized guest accelerator handling (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2886 by @thisjulio, https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2883 by @vdmgolub).
* **User interface fixes:** Enhanced the use of the `GetOutputs` option (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2881 by @hugorut).
* **Codebase refactoring:** Improved Azure resource migration for maintainability (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2901 by @aliscott).
* **Cloudformation provider:** fixed providers so that it no longer contains path error (https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2880 by  @haarchri)

### New Contributors

A big thank you to @thisjulio and @haarchri for their fantastic contributions! 🎉

**For the complete changelog, visit:** https://github.com/infracost/infracost/compare/v0.10.33...v0.10.34

name: v0.10.33
body:
# Infracost v0.10.33

This release introduces improvements to project auto-detection and performance enhancements. These updates are designed to make the tool more efficient and easier to use, particularly for users with complex infrastructure setups. The release also includes new support for cloud resources and addresses several important bug fixes.

### ☁️ Cloud Resources
- Added support for AWS Certificate Authority short-lived certificates by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2864.
- Fixed pricing for Azure MySQL/Postgres flexible servers by @vdmgolub in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2844.
- Added AWS `ca-west-1` region by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2866.

### 🪄 Auto-detection
- Added auto-detect cousin support by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2845.
- Introduced support for directory named environments by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2847.
- Added path_overrides autodetect configuration by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2853.
- Added terragrunt auto-detect support by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2841.
- Introduced tfvars.json autodetected variable support by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2869.
- Added fallback to include all paths functionality by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2868.
- Enhanced support for recognizing environment names from variable file suffixes by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2840.
- Matched tfvar naming to project names by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2850.
- Added skip auto detection for autogenerated config files by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2848.
- Corrected the error handling for empty projects in generate config by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2846.
- Corrected global var file exclusion from path_overrides by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2855.
- Fixed environment matching logic by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2851.

### ⚡ Performance
- Resolved memory leaks by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2849.
- Improved resource data loading efficiency by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2852.

### ⛰️ Other
- Added `tags_all` support for plan JSON runs by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2854.
- Introduced `--format=json` flag option to upload and comment commands by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2872 and https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2874.
- Fixed handling of child block inconsistent list elements by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2865.
- Addressed concurrent map read and write error by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2867.

**[Full Changelog](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/compare/v0.10.32...v0.10.33)**

name: v0.10.30
body:
## What's Changed
In this release, we're excited to introduce integrations with the [Infracost Cloud’s new FinOps policy checker](https://www.infracost.io/blog/finops-policies-automate-best-practices-now/). This allows you to check for FinOps best practices directly in engineering workflows.

## New Features:
- **FinOps policy checks**: Introduced FinOps policies and governance checks, thanks to @tim775. This includes support for handling FinOps policy exclusions and nested policy allow lists. ([#2661](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2661), [#2671](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2671), [#2678](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2678), [#2701](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2701))
- **AWS Kinesis Stream Resource**: Now supporting AWS Kinesis Stream Resources, thanks to the contribution from @ktasper. ([#2640](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2640))

## Enhancements:
- **Additional Azure Service Plan SKUs**: Added support for additional Azure service plan SKUs, implemented by @tim775. ([#2658](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2658))
- **Terragrunt Support**: Improved support for Terragrunt, including the ability to handle generate blocks and optional dependencies by @aliscott ([#2708](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2708))
- **Google User Labels as Tags**: Now supporting Google user labels as tags. Thanks to @tim775 for this enhancement. ([#2652](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2652))
- **Storage Account Refs for Storage Management Policies**: Enhanced support for storage account references in storage management policies, thanks to @tim775. ([#2695](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2695))
- **Support for Prefixes in Terraform Source Map**: Introduced support for prefixes in `INFRACOST_TERRAFORM_SOURCE_MAP`, implemented by @aliscott. ([#2693](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2693))

## Fixes:
- **Concurrent Map Writes Panic**: Fixed an issue with concurrent map writes by @aliscott. ([#2669](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2669))
- **Module `for_each` bug**: Fixed modules with `for_each` based on other module outputs by @aliscott. ([#2696](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2696))
- **Bug Fixes**: Addressed a typo in an error message and ensured the correct mapping URL is built if the mapped source contains a ref. Work done by @0o001 and @hugorut. ([#2654](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2654), [#2656](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2656))
- **Google Sustained Use Discount Calculation**: Fixed the calculation of Google Sustained Use Discounts, thanks to @varshneydevansh. ([#2577](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2577))

## Dependency Updates:
- Updated various dependencies, ensuring we are using the latest and most secure versions of libraries and tools.

## Miscellaneous:
- **Code and Test Maintenance**: Conducted code clean-up, removed unnecessary verbose flags from tests, added parser benchmarks, and fixed tests. Thanks to @tim775 and @hugorut for their contributions.
- **Improved Telemetry**: Adjusted telemetry settings for FinOps policy errors to enhance user privacy. ([#2704](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2704))

## New Contributors
* @0o001 made their first contribution in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2654
* @ktasper made their first contribution in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2640

We're thankful to all contributors who helped in making this release possible. Enjoy the enhanced experience and features of Infracost!

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/infracost/infracost/compare/v0.10.29...v0.10.30

name: v0.10.29

# Infracost v0.10.29

In this new release, we've concentrated on enhancing [tag policy support](https://www.infracost.io/docs/infracost_cloud/tagging_policies/). Furthermore, we've added a CLI cache to enhance the speed and efficiency of pricing lookups. Users should see a noticeable performance improvement when they upgrade.

### New Features
- Implemented a pricing client cache to improve performance by [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2629).
- Introduced support for applying tag policies to AWS launch templates by [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2611).
- Added block device tags to the AWS instance resource by [@tim775](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2613).
- Added the `il-central-1` region by [@aliscott](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2628).

### Enhancements
- Enhanced data block functionality in submodules to return correct values from stubbed data blocks by [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2616).
- Introduced support for optional defaults by [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2620).
- Refactored the comment handler to include backoff retry logic by [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2614).
- Conducted formatting adjustments by [@tim775](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2632).
  
### Fixes
- Fixed a race condition issue by ensuring terragrunt sources are downloaded only once by [@tim775](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2618).
- Addressed an issue that caused a panic due to incorrect variable type definition by [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2625).
- Resolved issues related to invalid function arguments in mocking by [@aliscott](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2627).
- Fixed the handling of un-Rel-able paths by [@tim775](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2630).

**[Full Changelog](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/compare/v0.10.28...v0.10.29)**

name: v0.10.27
body:
# Infracost v0.10.27

This release provides several enhancements and additions that aim to improve tag policies' efficiency and control. This includes support for `data.aws_default_tags` and various adjustments to tag handling at launch and within volume resources.

## New Features 🎁

- Support for `data.aws_default_tags` block has been added for improved tag coverage of resources. [PR #2597](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2597)
- Introducing various read file functions to give you more ways to interact with your local files in Infracost config template. [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2595)
- Infracost tagging policies now handle volume tags, allowing for better resource management and discovery. [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2599)
- Added support for `aws_launch_template` `tag_specifications`. [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2600)

## Enhancements 🔧

- You can now enjoy Terragrunt global cache for modules for more efficient module management. [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2584)
- We've updated the Tag Policy comment format, it now shows the value of any invalid tags that don't adhear to a tagging policy. [@vdmgolub](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2586)

## Fixes 🩹

- Stripping count from module name as configuration key when marshalling has been fixed. Improving overall estimates for users who saw discrepancies with modules using `count` and `for_each` [@vdmgolub](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2589)
- `aws_autoscaling_group` tag blocks that are have `progagate_at_launch` = `false` now fail tag policies. [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2598)

## Chores

- We've added memory and CPU profiling options to help with performance troubleshooting. [@hugorut](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2585)
- To prevent redundancy, we now skip commenting if the run was done earlier. [@aliscott](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2587)

For the full list of changes, check out the [changelog](https://github.com/infracost/infracost/compare/v0.10.26...v0.10.27).

name: v0.10.17
body:
# 0.10.17 (Feb 07 2023)

Infracost version `0.10.17` includes several enhancements and bug fixes aimed at helping users with complex setups. This version has improved support for module evaluation, error reporting, and pricing lookups. Give it a try!

## New features
* Augment the infracost comment command to allow passing client certificates for GitHub Enterprise Servers that require them - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2256
* Add support for absolute file paths for Terraform variable files, offering greater flexibility for projects and helping users with a top-level global variable file directory - by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2279
* Scope CLI run errors by project, so that multi-project runs no longer fail at the first error. Instead, they report aggregated errors at the end of the run, as shown in the example below:
  ```bash
  Project: infracost/infracost/cmd/infracost/testdata/breakdown_multi_project_with_error/dev
  Module path: dev
  
  Errors:
    Error loading Terraform modules:
       failed to inspect module path testdata/breakdown_multi_project_with_error/dev diag:
         Invalid block definition:
           Either a quoted string block label or an opening brace ("{") is expected here. (and 1 other messages)
  
  ──────────────────────────────────
  Project: infracost/infracost/cmd/infracost/testdata/breakdown_multi_project_with_error/prod
  Module path: prod
  
   Name                                                   Monthly Qty  Unit   Monthly Cost 
                                                                                           
   aws_instance.web_app                                                                    
   ├─ Instance usage (Linux/UNIX, on-demand, m5.8xlarge)          730  hours     $1,121.28 
   ├─ root_block_device                                                                    
   │  └─ Storage (general purpose SSD, gp2)                        50  GB            $5.00 
   └─ ebs_block_device[0]                                                                  
      ├─ Storage (provisioned IOPS SSD, io1)                    1,000  GB          $125.00 
      └─ Provisioned IOPS                                         800  IOPS         $52.00 
                                                                                           
   Project total                                                                 $1,303.28 
  
   OVERALL TOTAL                                                                 $1,303.28 
  ```
  by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2225 and @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2268

### AWS

* Add support for Lambda ARM architectures - by @robh007 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2269
* Add support for `ap-southeast-4` region - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2280

## Enhancements

* Improve the macOS/Linux installer script to allow downloading any version. For example: `export INFRACOST_VERSION=v0.10.16; curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/infracost/infracost/master/scripts/install.sh | sh` - by @sylwit in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2251
* Remove sensitive variables from evaluation warnings, so that variables such as foo_token no longer trigger CLI warnings - by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2271
* Add retry logic to Terraform Cloud variable loading. This improves fall over logic for cases where Terraform Cloud API returns a malformed response/code - by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2272
* Add backoff logic to pricing API requests, meaning that slow or malformed Pricing API responses won't kill a CLI run -  by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2248

## Fixes
* Module `for_each` attributes were not expanding correctly if they relied on a referenced expanded module. This improvement will benefit users who heavily rely on composable modules - by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2232
* Change project paths to absolute path if initial `--config-file` path is abs. This fixes a regression that prevented GitHub action workflows building cost estimates - by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2234
* `infracost comment` hiding module path when projects are skipped - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2240
* Reload ModuleCall when `each.value` changes. This resolves bugs where the incorrect module inputs were passed before the references were expanded - by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2241
* Copy `CoreResource` before costing policy, preventing resource outputs being changed when reporting cost estimates to the CLI - by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2246

### Azure
* Mark MSSQL database as free when its SKU is ElasticPool - by @vdmgolub in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2253
* Repair price lookup for API Management - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2267
* SQL server cost component lookup - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2275
* Application Gateway v2 costs - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2278

name: v0.10.11
body:
## What's Changed

Infracost **0.10.11** contains significant updates to improve VCS detection. In addition, we've added the ability to override detection, which enables users to specify how they want their VCS data displayed in Infracost Cloud.

Users should be aware that with **0.10.11** release, the `vcsRepoUrl` metadata attribute has been changed to `vcsRepositoryUrl`:

```diff
{
    "vcsPullRequestUrl": "https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/42",
-   "vcsRepoUrl": "https://github.com/infracost/infracost.git",
+   "vcsRepositoryUrl": "https://github.com/infracost/infracost.git",
    "vcsProvider": "github",
    "vcsBaseBranch": "master",
    "vcsPullRequestTitle": "Some PR title",
    "vcsPullRequestId": "4321" 
    ...
}
```

## Infracost Cloud enhancements:

* Infracost CLI has improved metadata support, meaning more platforms and deployment systems work out of the box with Infracost Cloud. Additional VCS environment variables have also been added to the CLI. Users can use these to override Infracost VCS detection. A complete list of supported environment variables is below - see [our docs for examples](https://www.infracost.io/docs/features/environment_variables/#environment-variables-to-override-metadata):
  ```
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_PROVIDER`: can be "github", "gitlab", "azure_repos" or "bitbucket"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_REPOSITORY_URL`: HTTPS URL of the repository, e.g. "https://github.com/infracost/example-terraform"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_PULL_REQUEST_URL`: HTTP URL of the pull request, e.g. "https://github.com/alikhajeh1/example-terraform/pull/2"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_PULL_REQUEST_AUTHOR`: author username or full name of the pull request, e.g. "john190" or "John Smith"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_PULL_REQUEST_TITLE`: title of the pull request, e.g. "Increase IOPS"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_BRANCH`: name of the branch that was used to generate the estimate, e.g. "increase_iops"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_COMMIT_SHA`: long commit SHA of the branch that was used to generate the estimate, e.g. "1af413ad15ad6cbdfca667361231231231231231"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_COMMIT_MESSAGE`: the commit message, e.g. "use m5.large"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_COMMIT_TIMESTAMP`: unix epoch timestamp of the commit, e.g. `1661801540`. You can use the following command to get the timestamp on the latest commit from the current branch `export INFRACOST_VCS_COMMIT_TIMESTAMP=$(git show -s --format=%ct)`
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_COMMIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL`: git email of author of the commit, e.g. "john@company.com"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_COMMIT_AUTHOR_NAME`: git author name of the commit, e.g. "John Smith"
  - `INFRACOST_VCS_PIPELINE_RUN_ID`: a way to differentiate pipelines that are run within one CI/CD run, this is the top-level pipeline ID, not individual jobs/runs within it, e.g. "2846680866"
  ```
  by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1990
* A new [`infracost upload` command](https://www.infracost.io/docs/features/cli_commands/#upload-runs) which supports uploading an Infracost JSON file to Infracost Cloud without the need for `infracost comment`. This command uploads the data regardless of your Org Settings or the `INFRACOST_ENABLE_CLOUD` environment variable. - by @tim775 in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1997

## New Features
 * Support for me-central-1, Middle East (UAE) region - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2001

## Fixes
 * Support case-insensitive Azure VM sizes - by @mnaghavi in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1994
 * Update `go-git` dependency to fix panics reported by Windows users - by @hugorut in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1989
 * Handle nested local object types when parsing HCL - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1972
 * Use correct object values when merging object context values - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1972
 * Fix Terragrunt parsing failure caused by incorrect assume role behaviour - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1977
 * Update `azurerm_function_app` and  `azurerm_mysql_flexible_server` price filters so they no longer show zero prices - by @aliscott in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1992

## New Contributors
* @mnaghavi made their first contribution in https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/1994

🐛 📉  Infracost **v0.10.9** contains a number of fixes for the CLI that are discovered when used with the [Infracost VS Code extension support](https://github.com/infracost/vscode-infracost).
